main event: Three irregularly shaped objects were observed over Grand Cayman Island from October 22 to 25, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were reported as moving slowly and changing direction., Some observers thought the objects could be aircraft while others disagreed., The weather at the time was described as normal., Observers likely did not have enough knowledge to fully evaluate the sighting., The case was ultimately listed as insufficient data.
witness description: observers likely lacked sufficient knowledge of higher atmospheric phenomena
